        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Code verification acceptance criteria for MRL 5",
        "description": "Observed order of accuracy must be within 5% of theoretical order for all governing equations. MMS residuals must converge to machine precision for steady manufactured solutions."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation performed on three systematically refined meshes (4.2M, 12.1M, 34.8M cells). Grid convergence index (GCI) for NIH is 1.4% on the fine mesh; GCI for wall shear stress is 2.1%. Achieved level 4 exceeds the required level 3, providing additional confidence margin for the Class III device context.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/discretization-error-mrl5",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria for MRL 5",
        "description": "GCI on primary QoI (NIH) must be less than 5% on the production mesh. Richardson extrapolation must use at least three systematically refined meshes with refinement ratio >= 1.3."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Bench test conditions (temperature 37±0.5°C, hematocrit 30±1%, bovine blood viscosity characterized by rheometry) are documented with measurement uncertainty. Operating points span the full VAD envelope (2–6 L/min, 2000–3600 RPM). Calibration records for all instruments traceable to NIST.",
